<br>
Trakanon: Venril Sathir is FCFS, and how many times has an ubreguild gone to take him out? Not many, and Trakanon would probably follow suite. Face it, Veeshan's Peak is a weak zone (lots of effort for very little), so it's not like there is a high demand to get a whole guild outfitted in VP keys. I'm sure there has been under 5 raids total to that zone since the zone went live. /shrug<br>
<br>
Sky: Extremely underused as it is, reservations here really don't seem to matter, since they are hardly ever bothered with. Removing them would do absolutely nothing in general, except make it easier for the rare raids to actually go up.<br>
<br>
Yes, this post supports FCFS, they are my opinions and I stand by them. This is not meant to become a rant, but is instead discussion-based.<br>
